
[1]personify

   PERSON'IFY, v.t. [L. persona and facio.] To give animation to inanimate
   objects; to ascribe to an inanimate being the sentiments, actions or
   language of a rational being or person,or to represent an inanimate
   being with the affections and actions of a person. Thus we say, the
   plants thirst for rain.

   The trees said to the fig-tree, come thou, and reign over us. Judges 9.
